title: Electronic Health Record Sharing System commences operation
content_text:
p>
	Commencing operation today (March 13), the Government's Electronic Health 
	Record Sharing System (eHRSS) provides a platform for health record sharing 
	between public and private healthcare organisations with patients' consent. 
	This will enable healthcare providers to provide better and more timely 
	treatment for patients. The system is a territory-wide patient-oriented healthcare infrastructure, 
	which will enhance the continuity of care, promote public-private 
	partnership and improve the quality of healthcare services. Registration is

partnership and improve the quality of healthcare services. Registration is 
	voluntary and free of charge. All 11 local private hospitals have registered to join eHRSS. 
	Pre-registration of healthcare providers (HCPs) and patients who had joined 
	the existing Public-Private Interface - Electronic Patient Record Sharing 
	Pilot Project (PPI-ePR) with the new system has taken place in stages since

commencing in December last year. The response so far has been positive. As at March 10, more than 240 HCPs of PPI-ePR have applied to join eHRSS; of 
	these, about 60 have completed registration. These HCPs include group 
	practices, solo practitioners and other healthcare organisations, such as 
	the health services in educational institutions and elderly care service 
	providers. In addition, about 22 000 PPI-ePR patients have registered for

migration to eHRSS. To encourage more people to participate in eHRSS, the Government will 
	conduct a series of promotional activities in the coming months, including 
	setting up registration booths or arranging mobile registration teams to 
	help the public to register at various service locations of the Hospital 
	Authority and the Department of Health, and elderly homes. The public may 
	also register with the sharing system through visiting the Electronic Health 
	Record Registration Centres, applying online, or submitting applications by 
	post, fax or drop-in box.
